Defendant Lashawn Maurice Owens in court with attorney Michael Jude.  Defendant Lashawn Maurice Owens in custody.  Daniel J. Gabler appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk ssm.

AS TO COUNT 2:  Pursuant to plea negotiations and on motion of the State, Court ordered count dismissed and read-in.

AS TO COUNT 1:  Defendant changes his plea to GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty.   Defendant advised that if not a United States Citizen, deportation is possible.  Court found that defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights.  Guilty Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.  Court found the state has satisfied victims' rights law.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  Defendant sentenced to serve 9 months in the House of Correction CONSECUTIVE to any other sentence.  Court STAYED the sentence and placed defendant on Probation with the State of Wisconsin, Department of Corrections for a period of 12 months.
Conditions:  
*  Pay restitution in the amount of $250.00 to Thomas P. or, if not paid, convert to a civil judgment;
*  AODA assessment/treatment deemed appropriate;
*  Maintain absolute sobriety to be monitored by random urine screens;
*  Follow through on any recommendations;
*  Write a letter of apology to Anita A.;
*  Pay all costs and surcharges or, if not paid, convert to a civil judgment.
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief received and filed.
